This is what you demo to the judges. It‚Äôs not just a website; it‚Äôs a **Decision Support System**.

### üö© The Red-Flag Engine (Logic Flow)

The backend runs a background cron job (or simple trigger) that calculates:


* **Logic:** If a project has spent  of its money but is only  done, the  spikes, the marker on the map turns **Bright Red**, and an email is sent to the Department Head.

### üì∏ The Verification Logic (My Added Idea)

To prevent "Paper Progress" (lying on forms):

1. Contractor uploads an image of the road.
2. The system extracts **EXIF Data** (GPS Lats/Longs).
3. **Validation:** If the photo's GPS coordinates are  away from the actual project site, the upload is **Rejected**.

---

## üíª 3. Technical Roadmap (The "How it Works" Stack)

| Component | Tech Used | Purpose |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Frontend** | React.js + Tailwind | Fast, responsive, and "Gov-Portal" professional look. |
| **Mapping** | Leaflet.js / OpenStreetMap | Plotting project coordinates visually. |
| **Data Viz** | Chart.js / Recharts | Turning boring budget numbers into visual "Burn-down" charts. |
| **Backend** | Node.js + Express | Handling the Red-Flag logic and API calls. |
| **Database** | MongoDB Atlas | Storing flexible project schemas and user roles. |
| **Storage** | Cloudinary / AWS S3 | To store the "Proof of Work" images uploaded by contractors. |

